    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-03-05T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-03-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="505"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d505">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Gresham</persName> to Baron
                            <persName type="to">Saurma</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-03-05">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 5, 1895</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 21.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Excellency</hi>: Referring to your note of the 22d ultimo,
                    and the Department’s reply thereto of the 1st instant, relating to the
                    invitation to this Government by His Majesty the Emperor to participate in the
                    ceremonies attending the opening of the Northern Baltic Canal in the latter part
                    of June next, I have now the honor to inform you, in view of a letter addressed
                    to this Department by the Secretary of the Navy, that Rear-Admiral U. A.
                    Kirkland, U. S. N., commander in chief United States naval force on the European
                    station, will be instructed to proceed to Kiel with the U. S. flagship <hi
                        rend="italic">San Francisco</hi>, under the command of Capt. E. M. Shepard,
                    U. S. N., and the <hi rend="italic">Marblehead</hi>, under the command of
                    Commander Charles O’Neil, U. S. N., for the purpose of taking part in the
                    proposed ceremony.</p>
                <p>Accept, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">W. Q. Gresham</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
